<!-- Definition and symptoms -->
'''Malaria''' nye  [[Mosquito-borne disease|mosquito-borne infectious disease]] na amegbetɔwo kple la bubuwo si tsoa parasitic [[protozoans]] (a type of single cell [[microorganism]]) na ''[[Plasmodium]]'' gbɔ.<ref name=WHO2014/> Malaria hea dzesiwo abe [[fever]], [[malaise|fatigue]], [[vomiting]] and [[headache]]s.<!-- <ref name=EBMED2014/> --> Le eƒe ŋusɛ̃ nu la, ehea [[jaundice|yellow skin]], [[seizure]]s, [[coma]] or [[death]].<ref name=EBMED2014/> Dzesi siawo dzea egɔme enuenu tso ŋkeke ewo yiɖe ŋkeke wuiatɔ le mu ƒe ameɖuɖu megbe.<!-- <ref name=WHO2014/> --> Dɔlele dzesiwo agatrɔ va le ɣletiwo megbe ne ame aɖe mexɔ dɔyɔyɔ blibo o.<ref name=WHO2014/> Le amesiwo me dɔlelea vɔ le la, egbugbɔ lele nu mesena o.<!-- <ref name=EBMED2014/> --> Dɔ malemale [[immunity|resistance]] nɔnɔme sia dzona le ɣeyiyi abe ɣletiwo kple ƒewo me ne nye be malaria mega le ame o.<ref name=EBMED2014/>

<!--Cause and diagnosis-->
Zi geɖee la, woxɔa dɔlele sia tso munɔ si ŋu dɔlelea le ƒe ameɖuɖu gbɔ''[[Anopheles]]'' mosquito.<!-- <ref name=WHO2014/> --> Ameɖuɖu sia ɖea parasitewo tso mu ƒe ta me ɖe ame ƒe [[circulatory system|blood]].<ref name=WHO2014/>me. Parasitewo zɔa yi na akla gbɔ afisi wotsina hedzi na ɖo.<!-- <ref name=EBMED2014/> --> ''Plasmodium'' ƒe ƒome atɔ ateŋu ahe dɔlele ve eye amegbetɔwo ma ne.<ref name=EBMED2014/> Ame ƒe kuku geɖe tso ''[[Plasmodium falciparum|P. falciparum]]'' with ''[[Plasmodium vivax|P. vivax]]'', ''[[Plasmodium ovale|P. ovale]]'' gbɔ, eye ''[[Plasmodium malariae|P. malariae]]'' hea malaria si ŋu ŋuse mele o la ve.<ref name=WHO2014/><ref name=EBMED2014/> ''[[Plasmodium knowlesi|P. knowlesi]]'' ƒomewo mena dɔlele amegbetɔwo kabakaba o.<ref name=WHO2014/> Wokpɔna malaria to ʋumedodo tso [[blood film]]s, alo kple [[antigen]]-based [[Malaria antigen detection tests|rapid diagnostic tests]].<ref name=EBMED2014/> Wowɔ mɔnusiwo woaza [[polymerase chain reaction]] atsɔ kpɔ parasite ƒe [[DNA]] , gake mebɔ ɖe afisiwo malaria [[Endemic (epidemiology)|common]] le o elabena woxɔ si eye womele bɔbɔe o.<ref name="Nadjm 2012">{{Cite journal |author=Nadjm B, Behrens RH |title=Malaria: An update for physicians |journal=Infectious Disease Clinics of North America |year=2012 |volume=26 |issue=2 |pages=243–59 |pmid=22632637 |doi=10.1016/j.idc.2012.03.010}}</ref>

<!--Prevention and treatment-->
Woateŋu aɖekpɔtɔ dɔa ƒe lele to mu ƒe amemaɖumaɖu me le  [[mosquito net]]wo kple [[insect repellent]]wo zaza me, alo to mu ƒe dzidzi tsotsoɖa mɔnuwo dzi abe [[insecticide]]wo  sisi kple tsimatsamatsawo ƒe ɖeɖeɖa.<ref name=EBMED2014/> Atikewɔwɔ na malaria nutsitsi ƒe mɔnuvovowo li [[malaria prophylaxis|prevent malaria]] na mɔzɔla siwo yina afisi dɔlelea le.<!-- <ref name=WHO2014/> --> Enye didi be woaza atikea [[sulfadoxine/pyrimethamine]] na [[infant]]wo kple funɔwo le [[first trimester]] ƒe [[pregnancy]] le teƒesiwo malaria bɔ ɖo.<!-- <ref name=WHO2014/> --> Togbɔ be ehia ha la, [[vaccine]] aɖeke meli o, gake agbagbadzedze na eƒe wɔwɔ le edzi yim.<ref name=WHO2014/> Malaria ƒe atike si dzi woda asi ɖoe nye ƒuƒoƒo na [[antimalarial medication]]wo siwo me [[artemisinin]] le.<ref name=WHO2014/><ref name=EBMED2014/> Atikewɔwɔ evelia enye  [[mefloquine]], [[lumefantrine]], alo sulfadoxine/pyrimethamine.<ref name=WHO2010>{{cite book|last1=Organization|first1=World Health|title=Guidelines for the treatment of malaria|date=2010|publisher=World Health Organization|location=Geneva|isbn=9789241547925|page=ix|edition=2nd ed.}}</ref> Woateŋu aza[[Quinine]] kpeɖe [[doxycycline]] ne artemisinin meli o.<ref name=WHO2010/> Le teƒe siwo dɔlelea bɔ ɖo la, ehia be woakpɔ malaria hafi woadze atike zaza me ɖe atike ƒe dɔmawɔmawɔ ta [[drug resistance]].<!-- <ref name=WHO2014/> -->Atikewo ƒe dɔmawɔmawɔ he malaria ƒe atikewɔwɔ geɖewo ve; le kpɔɖeŋu me, [[chloroquine]]-resistant ''P. falciparum'' kaka yiɖe malaria nɔƒe geɖewo, eye resistance na artemisinin va zu problem le Anyigbeɣedzeƒe Asia ƒe akpa aɖewo.<ref name=WHO2014/>

<!--Epidemiology-->
Dɔlelea bɔ ɖe [[Tropics|tropical]] kple [[subtropical]] nutome siwo te ɖe [[equator]] la me.<ref name=EBMED2014>{{cite journal|last=Caraballo|first=Hector|title=Emergency Department Management Of Mosquito-Borne Illness: Malaria, Dengue, And West Nile Virus|journal=Emergency Medicine Practice|date=May 2014|volume=16|issue=5|url=http://www.ebmedicine.net/topics.php?paction=showTopic&topic_id=405}}</ref> Eɖewoe nye [[Sub-Saharan Africa]], [[Asia]], and [[Latin America]].<!-- <ref name=WHO2014/> --> [[World Health Organization]] bui be le ƒe 2012 me la, malaria le ame million 207 .<!-- <ref name=WHO2014/> --> Le ƒema me la, dɔa wu ame abe tso 473,000 yi 789,000 ene siwodometɔ geɖe nye ɖeviwo tso Africa.<ref name=WHO2014>{{cite web|title=Malaria  Fact sheet N°94|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs094/en/|website=WHO|accessdate=28 August 2014|date=March 2014}}</ref> Malaria kple ahedada wodoa ka ɖeka eye wogblea nu le [[economic development]] ŋu.<ref name="IftSoL">{{Cite report |author=Gollin D, Zimmermann C |title=Malaria: Disease Impacts and Long-Run Income Differences |date=August 2007 |publisher=[[Institute for the Study of Labor]] |url=http://ftp.iza.org/dp2997.pdf |format=PDF}}</ref><ref name="Worrall 2005">{{Cite journal |author=Worrall E, Basu S, Hanson K |title=Is malaria a disease of poverty? A review of the literature |journal=Tropical Health and Medicine |year=2005 |volume=10 |issue=10 |pages=1047–59 |doi=10.1111/j.1365-3156.2005.01476.x |pmid=16185240}} {{open access}}</ref> Le Africa la, wobuibe egblea ga woade abe $12 billion USD le ƒe ɖeka me to eƒe dada , dɔmateŋuwɔwɔ kple nugbegble le tourism ŋu la me.<ref name="Greenwood 2005">{{Cite journal |author=Greenwood BM, Bojang K, Whitty CJ, Targett GA |title=Malaria |journal=Lancet |year=2005|volume=365 |issue=9469 |pages=1487–98 |pmid=15850634 |doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(05)66420-3}}</ref>

